KEY_MAX_ALLOCATION_MB_TIP: The per queue maximum limit of memory to allocate to each container request at the Resource Manager. This setting overrides the cluster configuration yarn.scheduler.maximum-allocation-mb. This value must be smaller than or equal to the cluster maximum. No limit of memory/cores if set to -1
KEY_MAX_ALLOCATION_VCORES_TIP: The per queue maximum limit of virtual cores to allocate to each container request at the Resource Manager. This setting overrides the cluster configuration yarn.scheduler.maximum-allocation-vcores. This value must be smaller than or equal to the cluster maximum. No limit of memory/cores if set to -1
KEY_INACTIVE_QUEUE_WARNING: There is inactive queue. Need to restart service to activate it
KEY_YARN_QUOTA_CAPACITY_CUSTOM_CONFIG_TI: config name muse be legal. for example, yarn.scheduler.minimum-allocation-mb
KEY_YARN_QUOTA_FAIR_CUSTOM_CONFIG_TIP: config name muse be legal. for example, yarn.scheduler.fair.preemption
KEY_YARN_QUOTA_CAPACITY_CUSTOM_CONFIG_TI: config name muse be legal. for example, yarn.scheduler.minimum-allocation-mb
KEY_YARN_QUOTA_FAIR_CUSTOM_CONFIG_TIP2: if config is XML config, the value can be in XML. Guardian will generate <config>configValue</config>. For example, we have a config named selfDefinedConf value of `<conf>300</conf>`，guardian will generate `<selfDefinedConf><conf>300</conf></selfDefinedConf>` for that config
KEY_CAPACITY_GLOBAL_RESOURCE_CALCULATOR_: The ResourceCalculator implementation to be used to compare Resources in the scheduler. The default i.e. org.apache.hadoop.yarn.util.resource.DefaultResourseCalculator only uses Memory while DominantResourceCalculator uses Dominant-resource to compare multi-dimensional resources such as Memory, CPU etc. A Java ResourceCalculator class name is expected.
KEY_CAPACITY_GLOBAL_NODE_LOCALITY_DELAY_: Number of missed scheduling opportunities after which the CapacityScheduler attempts to schedule rack-local containers. Typically, this should be set to number of nodes in the cluster. By default is setting approximately number of nodes in one rack which is 40. Positive integer value is expected.
KEY_CAPACITY_GLOBAL_MAXIMUM_AM_RESOURCE_: Maximum percent of resources in the cluster which can be used to run application masters - controls number of concurrent active applications. Limits on each queue are directly proportional to their queue capacities and user limits. Specified as a float - ie 0.5 = 50%. Default is 10%. This can be set for all queues with yarn.scheduler.capacity.maximum-am-resource-percent and can also be overridden on a per queue basis by setting yarn.scheduler.capacity.<queue-path>.maximum-am-resource-percent
KEY_CAPACITY_GLOBAL_QUEUE_MAPPINGS_TIP: This configuration specifies the mapping of user or group to aspecific queue. You can map a single user or a list of users to queues. Syntax: [u or g]:[name]:[queue_name][,next_mapping]*. Here, u or g indicates whether the mapping is for a user or group. The value is u for user and g for group. name indicates the user name or group name. To specify the user who has submitted the application, %user can be used. queue_name indicates the queue name for which the application has to be mapped. To specify queue name same as user name, %user can be used. To specify queue name same as the name of the primary group for which the user belongs to, %primary_group can be used.
KEY_CAPACITY_GLOBAL_MAXIMUM_APPLICATIONS: Maximum number of applications in the system which can be concurrently active both running and pending. Limits on each queue are directly proportional to their queue capacities and user limits. This is a hard limit and any applications submitted when this limit is reached will be rejected. Default is 10000. This can be set for all queues with yarn.scheduler.capacity.maximum-applications and can also be overridden on a per queue basis by setting yarn.scheduler.capacity.<queue-path>.maximum-applications. Integer value expected.
KEY_CAPACITY_GLOBAL_QUEUE_MAPPINGS_OVERR: This function is used to specify whether the user specified queues can be overridden. This is a Boolean value and the default value is false.
KEY_CAPACITY_TIP: Queue Capacity(In Percentage), 12.5 stands for 12.5% i.e. And sum of all queues of the same level must be 100.
KEY_MAX_CAPACITY_TIP: When there is free resource in cluster, Queue can expand its capacity. Max Capacity restrict maximum capacity it can use(In Percentage). Default -1 means don't allow capacity expanding.
KEY_USER_LIMIT_TIP: Resource Limit for every user(In Percentage). Round to integer. Default 100 means no limit
KEY_USER_LIMIT_FACTOR_TIP: Resource Limit for every user is USER_LIMIT_FACTOR * QUEUE_CAPACITY. Factor greater than 1 means allowing user use capacity exceeding Queue's capacity. Default 1 menas not allowing exceeding Queue's capacity.
KEY_MAX_APPLICATION_AMOUNT_TIP: Max number of running and pending application in a Queue. This is a strong constraint. For a cluster, once the application number reach the limit, the subsequent submitted application will be rejected
KEY_MAX_APPLICATION_MASTER_RESOURCE_TIP: Max resource value of Application Master when running(In Percentage). Value in decimal. 0.5 stands for 50%.  Default 0.1.
KEY_STATUS_TIP: Queue's state，If it is set to 'STOPPED', new application can not submit to the Queue and its decendants. Running application will continue execute
KEY_WEIGHT_TIP: Resource allocation weight. Default 1. Queue with weight 2 will be given twice resource of Queue with weight 1.
KEY_MIN_VCORE_TIP: Min CPU core allocation for Queue
KEY_MAX_VCORE_TIP: Max CPU core allocation for Queue
KEY_SCHEDULE_POLICY_TIP: Fair Scheduling Policy decides the resource allocation. FIFO Policy allocate resource depending on application's submission time. Submission get resource in order of time. Dominant Resource Fairness(DRF) will concern memory and CPU
KEY_MIN_PTIME_TIP: If Queue resource allocation is below minimum resource allocation in Min Share Preemption Time, the Queue will start to preempt resource.
KEY_DEFAULT_QUEUE_TIP: SQL task will be submitted to default queue. All users have permission to submit tasks to the default queue despite the queue permission constraint. must be leaf node
KEY_WEIGHT_FURION_TIP: Default by 1. Bigger weight means higher scheduling priority.
KEY_RESERVE_CPU_NUMBER_TIP: Reserved CPU number for this specific queue. Not shared with other queue.
KEY_RESERVE_CPU_PERCENT_TIP: Reserved CPU percent for this specific queue.(relative to CPU resource of the cluster). Not shared with other queue.
KEY_MAX_CPU_NUMBER_TIP: Max CPU number for the queue. Tasks of the queue cannot hold more CPU number than Max CPU number.
KEY_MAX_CPU_PERCENT_TIP: Max CPU percent for the queue.(relative to CPU resource of the cluster) Tasks of the queue cannot hold more CPU resource than Max CPU percent resource.
KEY_SCHEDULE_POLICY_FURION_TIP: FIFO schedules tasks according to submit time. Fair schedules tasks entirely fairly.
KEY_YARN_QUOTA_SCHEDULER_EDIT_TIP_CAPACI: Need to activate queue after add child queue for root queue. Need to restart yarn after add child queue for non-root queue.
KEY_YARN_QUOTA_SCHEDULER_EDIT_TIP_FAIR: Need to restart yarn after delete child queue of root queue. Need to activate queue after delete child queue of non-root queue.
KEY_INCEPTOR_QUOTA_SCHEDULER_EDIT_TIP_FU: Need to restart inceptor after delete queue
KEY_EDIT_ADMIN_ROLE_DESC: Selected users will have this system role
KEY_SUPER_ADMIN_DESC: Has all permission of the system
KEY_PERM_ADMIN_DESC: Can manage resource's permission and quota
KEY_PERM_VIEWER_DESC: Can view resource's permission and quota
KEY_PWD_MIN_AGE_DESC: The minimum time the password can be modified again
KEY_PWD_MAX_AGE_DESC: The maximum time the password can be used before expired.
KEY_PWD_IN_HISTORY_DESC: The saved password count in history
KEY_PWD_EXPIRE_WARNING_DESC: 'n' represents the field value. Users can receive password expiration waring after 'n' seconds before expiration day.
KEY_PWD_GRACE_LOGIN_LIMIT_DESC: The login times users can try after password is expired
KEY_PWD_LOCKOUT_DESC: If set 0, user will not be locked for password failure. If max failure time is set, user will be locked after fail more than max failure time.
KEY_PWD_LOCKOUT_DURATION_DESC: The duration of a user being locked
KEY_PWD_FAILURE_COUNT_INTERVAL_DESC: After the field value time, the failure counter of max failure time will be set zero.
KEY_PWD_MUST_CHANGE_DESC: if a user is a new user or his/her password is reset, he/she need to modify password after login.
KEY_PWD_SAFE_MODIFY_DESC: Users need to provide original password to modify password.
KEY_PWD_MIN_CLASSES_DESC: The minimum class of characters contained in user password, consisting of uppercase letter, lowercase letter, digit, punctuation and invisible character
KEY_TRUST_DOMAIN_TYPE_TIP: OUTGOING - Current domain trust remote domain. User from remote domain can access services of current domain. INCOMING - Remote domain trust current domain. User from current domain can access services of remote domain. Current domain adn remote domain trust each other. Users from two domains can access services of both domain.
KEY_CONFIRM_LOCK_TIPS: Confirm lock current user, this user can not login in system.
KEY_CONFIRM_UNLOCK_TIPS: Confirm unlock current user, this user can login in system again.
KEY_CONFIRM_DELETE_USER: Confirm delete current user, this user cannot login system.
KEY_CONFIRM_DELETE_PERM: Confirm delete this perm, this perm will remove from service
KEY_ADD_USER_GROUP_TIP: Please select group, and add this user to this group, then this user can share this group resource.
KEY_ADD_USER_ROLE_TIP: Please select role, and add this role to this user, then this user own this role.
KEY_ADD_GROUP_USER_TIP: Please select user and add user to this group, then the user can share group resource.
KEY_ADD_GROUP_ROLE_TIP: Please select role and add role to this group, then the user in the group have the role.
KEY_ADD_ROLE_USER_TIP: Please select user and add role to this user, then the user has the role.
KEY_ADD_ROLE_GROUP_TIP: Please select group and add role to this group, then the user in the group have the role.
KEY_USER_COUNT_TIP: Current own this role user count
KEY_GROUP_COUNT_TIP: Current own this role group count
KEY_POLICY_SOURCE_IP_TIP: Resources are accessible only if the requests are from allowed IPs
KEY_AUDIT_CONFIG_INFO1: Guardian server only record selected audit levels.
KEY_AUDIT_CONFIG_INFO2: Initial config is not persistent. If you want to persistency, please go TDH manager.
